text.section:
An applicant for a commercial driver's license shall pay the Administration the following fees established by the Administration:
Upon application for a new commercial driver's license or a commercial driver's license of a class other than that which the applicant holds:
The base license fee if a commercial driver's instructional permit is required or an amount established by the Administration if an instructional permit is not required;
A commercial driver's license fee; and
The applicable fees listed in subsection (b) of this section;
For the renewal of any class of commercial driver's license:
A renewal fee;
A commercial driver's license fee; and
The applicable fees listed in subsection (b) of this section;
For the conversion of a Maryland Class A, B, C, or D driver's license to a commercial driver's license:
A renewal fee;
A commercial driver's license fee; and
The applicable fees listed in subsection (b) of this section; and
For issuance of a duplicate or corrected commercial driver's license, a duplicate or corrected driver's license fee.
